{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pullrequests/274/comments/59234373.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/diff/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport:84d286a4cfef..d070978f7689?path=log%2Fsrc%2FPlayback.cc"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pull-requests/274/_/diff#comment-59234373"}}, "parent": {"id": 59096032, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pullrequests/274/comments/59096032.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pull-requests/274/_/diff#comment-59096032"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 274, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pullrequests/274.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pull-requests/274"}}, "title": "Logging Part 6: Playback ignition transport topics"}, "content": {"raw": "Alternatively, we could have `stop` be a `std::atomic_bool` instead of ordinary `bool`.\n\nI suspect it won't make a difference, since `bool` can't exist in a partially-written state, making it largely unaffected by race condition issues. Still, making it explicitly atomic would be good practice anyway.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Alternatively, we could have <code>stop</code> be a <code>std::atomic_bool</code> instead of ordinary <code>bool</code>.</p>\n<p>I suspect it won't make a difference, since <code>bool</code> can't exist in a partially-written state, making it largely unaffected by race condition issues. Still, making it explicitly atomic would be good practice anyway.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-03-19T17:26:25.653785+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Michael Grey", "uuid": "{c1cdfe52-2887-474c-ae99-72fdc53a59c9}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bc1cdfe52-2887-474c-ae99-72fdc53a59c9%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bc1cd